  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Teach Meditation to 25 Low-Income Urban Students</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children face indescribable daily stress in this country of social unrest and violence, where safety cannot always be found in school or at home. Quiet Time uses the practical, evidence-based Transcendental Meditation (TM) technique to reduce stress and dramatically improve academic performance, student wellness, and the school environment. The program brings two 15-minute meditation periods into the school day for urban middle and high school students at underserved schools across the country.</narrative>
  </description>
